query: INSERT INTO study_materials (
        tenant_id, exam, type, title, subject, chapter, description, s3_key, uploaded_by,
        subject_id_fk, chapter_id, topic_id, file_size_kb
      )
       VALUES ($1::uuid, 'jee'::study_materials_exam_enum, $2::study_materials_type_enum, $3, $4, $5, $6, '', $7, $8, $9, $10, 0)
       RETURNING id, title, type::text AS "fileType", description, topic_id AS "topicId" -- PARAMETERS: ["c259cd4e-b018-45e2-8e46-52a497ca49a1","dpp","DPP Sheet — Derivation","Math","Calculus","# CLASS 10 DPP -- Derivation\n**Subject:** Math | **Chapter:** Calculus | **Date:** 2024-02-20\n\n## Section A -- Multiple Choice (1 mark each)\n1. The process of finding the derivative of a function is called _______.\nA) Integration\nB) Differentiation\nC) Limit\nD) Function\n\n2. If f(x) = 3x^2, then f'(x) is _______.\nA) 3x\nB) 6x\nC) 9x\nD) 12x\n\n3. The derivative of x^n is _______.\nA) nx^(n-1)\nB) nx^(n+1)\nC) (n-1)x^n\nD) (n+1)x^n\n\n4. What is the derivative of sin(x) _______.\nA) cos(x)\nB) sin(x)\nC) tan(x)\nD) sec(x)\n\n5. The derivative of a constant is _______.\nA) 1\nB) 0\nC) x\nD) x^2\n\n## Section B -- Numericals / Short Answer (3 marks each)\n1. Find the derivative of the function f(x) = 2x^2 + 3x - 4.\n\n2. If f(x) = x^3 - 2x^2 + x - 1, find f'(x).\n\n3. Find the derivative of the function f(x) = sin(x) + cos(x).\n\n4. If f(x) = 3x^2 - 2x + 1, find f'(2).\n\n## Section C -- 5-mark questions\n1. Find the derivative of the function f(x) = (x^2 + 1) / (x + 1) using the quotient rule.\n\n2. If f(x) = x^4 - 2x^3 + x^2 - x + 1, find f'(x) and evaluate f'(1).\n\n3. Find the derivative of the function f(x) = sqrt(x) + 1/x.\n\n4. If f(x) = sin(2x), find f'(x) and evaluate f'(π/4).\n\n5. Find the derivative of the function f(x) = e^x + log(x).\n\n## Answer Key\n**Section A**\n1. B) Differentiation\n2. B) 6x\n3. A) nx^(n-1)\n4. A) cos(x)\n5. B) 0\n\n**Section B**\n1. f'(x) = 4x + 3\n2. f'(x) = 3x^2 - 4x + 1\n3. f'(x) = cos(x) - sin(x)\n4. f'(2) = 12 - 4 = 8\n\n**Section C**\n1. f'(x) = (2x(x+1) - (x^2+1)) / (x+1)^2 = (x^2 + 2x - 1) / (x+1)^2\n2. f'(x) = 4x^3 - 6x^2 + 2x - 1, f'(1) = 4 - 6 + 2 - 1 = -1\n3. f'(x) = 1/(2*sqrt(x)) - 1/x^2\n4. f'(x) = 2*cos(2x), f'(π/4) = 2*cos(π/2) = 0\n5. f'(x) = e^x + 1/x","526d9c0e-e2cd-4999-b1ec-a24646474796","6bda44a0-0523-42cc-90f6-97e50286b91e","38226e46-16eb-4cde-8ab2-31a3ac085c60","618980e3-0f96-4ab0-807d-c40b90cda631"]
