       RETURNING id, title, type::text AS "fileType", description, topic_id AS "topicId" -- PARAMETERS: ["c259cd4e-b018-45e2-8e46-52a497ca49a1","notes","Key Concepts — Derivation","Math","Calculus","### Introduction to Derivatives\n* **Derivative**: Measures the rate of change of a function with respect to one of its variables, units depend on the function, used to find the slope of a curve at a point.\n* **Limit**: The value that a function approaches as the input gets arbitrarily close to a certain point, no units, used to define the derivative of a function.\n* **Differentiation**: The process of finding the derivative of a function, no units, used to find the rate of change of a function.\n\n### Rules of Differentiation\n* **Power Rule**: If f(x) = x^n, then f'(x) = nx^(n-1), no units, used to differentiate polynomial functions.\n* **Product Rule**: If f(x) = u(x)v(x), then f'(x) = u'(x)v(x) + u(x)v'(x), no units, used to differentiate products of functions.\n* **Quotient Rule**: If f(x) = u(x)/v(x), then f'(x) = (u'(x)v(x) - u(x)v'(x)) / v(x)^2, no units, used to differentiate quotients of functions.\n* **Chain Rule**: If f(x) = g(h(x)), then f'(x) = g'(h(x)) * h'(x), no units, used to differentiate composite functions.\n\n### Geometric Interpretation of Derivatives\n* **Slope of a Curve**: The derivative of a function at a point represents the slope of the curve at that point, units of rise over run, used to find the steepness of a curve.\n* **Tangent Line**: The line that just touches a curve at a point and has the same slope as the curve at that point, no units, used to visualize the derivative of a function.\n* **Normal Line**: The line that is perpendicular to the tangent line at a point on a curve, no units, used to find the direction perpendicular to a curve.\n\n### Higher-Order Derivatives\n* **Second Derivative**: The derivative of the derivative of a function, units depend on the function, used to find the concavity of a curve.\n* **Higher-Order Derivatives**: The derivatives of a function beyond the second derivative, units depend on the function, used to find the higher-order properties of a curve.\n\n### Applications of Derivatives\n* **Maxima and Minima**: The points on a curve where the derivative is zero or undefined, no units, used to find the maximum or minimum value of a function.\n* **Optimization**: The process of finding the maximum or minimum value of a function subject to certain constraints, no units, used to solve real-world problems.\n* **Motion Along a Line**: The study of the motion of an object along a line, units of distance over time, used to model the motion of objects.\n* **Related Rates**: The study of the rates of change of related quantities, units depend on the quantities, used to solve problems involving rates of change.","526d9c0e-e2cd-4999-b1ec-a24646474796","6bda44a0-0523-42cc-90f6-97e50286b91e","38226e46-16eb-4cde-8ab2-31a3ac085c60","618980e3-0f96-4ab0-807d-c40b90cda631"]
