query: INSERT INTO study_materials (
        tenant_id, exam, type, title, subject, chapter, description, s3_key, uploaded_by,
        subject_id_fk, chapter_id, topic_id, file_size_kb
      )
       VALUES ($1::uuid, 'jee'::study_materials_exam_enum, $2::study_materials_type_enum, $3, $4, $5, $6, '', $7, $8, $9, $10, 0)
       RETURNING id, title, type::text AS "fileType", description, topic_id AS "topicId" -- PARAMETERS: ["c259cd4e-b018-45e2-8e46-52a497ca49a1","mindmap","Mindmap — Derivation","Math","Calculus","# Introduction to Calculus\n## Limits\n### Introduction to Limits\n- Definition of a limit\n- Notation of a limit\n- Basic properties of limits\n### Limits of Algebraic Functions\n- Limits of polynomial functions\n- Limits of rational functions\n- Limits of trigonometric functions\n### Limits of Trigonometric Functions\n- Limits of sine, cosine, and tangent functions\n- Limits of cosecant, secant, and cotangent functions\n### Sandwitch Theorem and Squeeze Theorem\n- Definition of the sandwitch theorem\n- Definition of the squeeze theorem\n- Applications of the sandwitch and squeeze theorems\n## Differentiation\n### Introduction to Differentiation\n- Definition of a derivative\n- Notation of a derivative\n- Basic properties of derivatives\n### Differentiation Rules\n- Power rule of differentiation\n- Product rule of differentiation\n- Quotient rule of differentiation\n- Chain rule of differentiation\n### Geometric Interpretation of Derivative\n- Tangent line to a curve\n- Slope of a curve\n- Equation of a tangent line\n### Higher Order Derivatives\n- Definition of higher order derivatives\n- Notation of higher order derivatives\n- Applications of higher order derivatives\n## Applications of Derivatives\n### Maxima and Minima\n- Definition of maxima and minima\n- First derivative test\n- Second derivative test\n- Applications of maxima and minima\n### Rate of Change\n- Instantaneous rate of change\n- Average rate of change\n- Applications of rate of change\n### Curve Sketching\n- Definition of curve sketching\n- Steps involved in curve sketching\n- Applications of curve sketching\n## Integration\n### Introduction to Integration\n- Definition of an integral\n- Notation of an integral\n- Basic properties of integrals\n### Integration Rules\n- Substitution method of integration\n- Integration by parts\n- Integration by partial fractions\n- Integration by trigonometric substitution\n### Definite Integrals\n- Definition of a definite integral\n- Notation of a definite integral\n- Applications of definite integrals\n### Applications of Integrals\n- Area under curves\n- Volume of solids\n- Surface area of solids\n- Applications of integrals in physics and engineering\n## Numerical Methods\n### Introduction to Numerical Methods\n- Definition of numerical methods\n- Importance of numerical methods\n- Basic numerical methods\n### Trapezoidal Rule and Simpson's Rule\n- Definition of the trapezoidal rule\n- Definition of Simpson's rule\n- Applications of the trapezoidal rule and Simpson's rule\n### Numerical Differentiation and Integration\n- Numerical differentiation\n- Numerical integration\n- Applications of numerical differentiation and integration","526d9c0e-e2cd-4999-b1ec-a24646474796","6bda44a0-0523-42cc-90f6-97e50286b91e","38226e46-16eb-4cde-8ab2-31a3ac085c60","618980e3-0f96-4ab0-807d-c40b90cda631"]
